{
  "stem": "13079.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But they were free to have brought to the court any witnesses of their choosing to be heard in their behalf.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "In other words, it was recognized that these trials were being held by a victor nation.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we wanted it to be thoroughly understood that these accused were being given the same or substantially the same rights that a citizen of the United States would have who has been charged with the commission of a crime in the Federal Courts.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And those guideposts prevailed in all four trials.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would say, basically that each trial was, while they were all concentration camps, there was differences.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the personnel that were brought to trial, they different just like day and night.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So there was no uniformity in the sense that when you heard one you heard it all.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because each one of the camps, being operated by different groups of accused, different types of conduct prevailed in each one of them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Michael Redwoods was, as I remember at this point, and he was an assistant Schutzhaftlagerfuhrer.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, my German is terrible.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I've got an Alabama accent.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I can't quite curl it over to speak the German that-- with the facility that probably I should.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But Redwoods was-- he was really the second highest [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] officer in charge of Dachau.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And being a Schutzhaftlagerfuhrer he carried out his duties as well prescribed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But he was unfortunately, like most of these accused, blood thirsty and mercy was not known to them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In Dachau, I prosecuted a man by the name of-- [LAUGHS] his name escapes from me at this moment-- Dr.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Karl Klaus Shilling.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Dr.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Shilling was a noted authority in the field of medicine relating to tropical diseases.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
